                        <p>
                            Envision Financial originated after the partnering of Delta Credit Union and First Heritage Savings. With roots in local agriculture and fishing industries, Envision is a member owned cooperative with a history of meeting British Columbians needs for 70 years. The founding credit unions were built by hardworking citizens who wanted a locally responsive financial institution that would work with them to achieve their goals, offering an alternative to big banks. Still today, Envision thrives with its proud history as a solid financial success, excellent employee wellbeing, corporate citizenship and inventive member services. In 2010, Envision partnered with Okanagan credit union Valley First, to create First West, B.C.’s third-largest credit union. Envision continues to support its local community, seeing themselves as a partner supporting charities and community events. Encouraging environmental and educational organizations as well as arts and culture, Envision helps non profit groups to continue their charitable work. Specifically tailored to education, Envision’s scholarship program offers to successful applicants thousands of dollars to help them finance post secondary academic pursuits. In 2013, Envision commenced a ten year project committed to raising $1,000,000 for local food banks. The Full Cupboard is an innovative community based program designed to engage employees, members and local partners to join the conversation about hunger in efforts to increase visibility.  Through helping their community partner, Food Banks BC, they are helping to serve around 100,000 clients annually. As part of First West, Envision continues to serve its members as a strong and responsive financial institution committed to exceptional service and community involvement.
                        </p>
